    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="461"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1354</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-27">May 27,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dr. T. V. Soong, Foreign Minister of China, accompanied by the Counselor, called
                    at my request.</p>
                <p>I handed the Minister the substance of the proposed lend-lease agreement between
                    this country and China, which he seemed pleased to receive.</p>
                <p>There were just a few general remarks exchanged since the Minister was obliged to
                    leave for a White House engagement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
